The Investment Banking Analyst role at Stifel GMP is both challenging and stimulating. At the early stages of their career, Analysts focus on maintaining/updating databases, client presentations, research, and financial modeling, As the individual’s career progresses, Analysts will be expected to take on increased responsibilities including managing live transactions and interacting with clients.
Stifel GMP has a strong position in the Canadian market and is continuing to grow by adding top talent. The role offers candidates an opportunity to gain valuable, hands-on work experience that is focused on the financial markets.
In Canada, we are primarily organized into industry teams focused on specific sectors. These include: Metals & Mining (Toronto, Vancouver), Diversified Industries (Toronto, Montreal, Vancouver), Life Sciences (Toronto), Technology (Toronto), Financial Institutions & Sponsors (Toronto), Quebec-based clients (Montreal) and Energy & Natural Resources (Calgary).
We are currently seeking a generalist candidate to support our Investment Banking franchise in Toronto.
Summary
The Investment Banking Analyst will be in charge of supporting the investment banking team with tasks that may include:
Analysis of financial, industry and market data;
Marketing, executing and structuring investment banking mandates focused on strategic and capital markets transactions;
Development of financial models related to company/asset valuations, capital raises, and merger and acquisition transactions;
Maintain proprietary databases including precedent transactions and market comparables;
Preparation of internal and external client presentations; and
Assisting in the generation of marketing materials including introductory presentations and confidential information memorandums.
Qualifications
A high regard for detail and accuracy are essential. The role of the Investment Banking Analyst is challenging and fast-paced. It requires dedication, passion for the industry, and a solid work ethic.
Educational credentials should consist of an undergraduate degree in business, with a focus on finance and a CFA or CPA designation or the pursuit of a CFA or CPA designation.
Summer/co-op or full-time work experience in corporate finance, investment banking, accounting or private equity is beneficial;
Strong financial/analytical skills related to corporate finance and securities analysis;
High degree of work ethic and motivation, including a willingness to work long hours;
Expertise with Microsoft Office applications including Excel, PowerPoint and Word;
Experience with financial markets software and applications including Bloomberg, FactSet and Capital IQ;
The ability to manage multiple tasks and meet deadlines;
Excellent interpersonal and communication skills;
Ability to work in an open office and team environment;
A track record of taking initiative;
A demonstrated proficiency in problem solving; and
A strong interest in and understanding of financial markets.
About STIFEL GMP
Stifel Canada (https://www.stifel.com/institutional/StifelCanada) is a leading provider of investment banking services, including advisory and underwriting, institutional sales and trading and research services. We offer a full suite of focused debt capital markets, equity capital markets, financial advisory, and investment services, delivering superior advice and execution to a broad range of corporate clients and institutional investors worldwide.
Stifel Canada is a subsidiary of Stifel Financial Corp., a full-service investment bank with over 600 investment banking professionals, international coverage and deep industry experience, serving the needs of middle-market companies through specialized expertise and strong relationships within its core industries. Stifel is ranked number one for total number of managed equity deals under $1 billion; ranked number two for managed venture capital-backed IPOs; and, ranked number one among middle-market investment banks for public M&A transactions under $1 billion.

